name: UI/UX Guidelines
description: Standards for frontend design and interaction.

---

General:
- Desktop-first, but fully responsive (mobile friendly)
- Stripe-style: clean, minimal, professional
- Consistent layout spacing and readable font hierarchy
- Use Tailwind utility classes for styling
- Animate with Framer Motion where applicable

Best Practices:
- Use skeletons or spinners for async loading
- Display clear, actionable error messages
- Avoid modals inside modals
- Use system-level feedback for saves, deletes, etc.
- Prioritize accessibility (`aria-*`, keyboard nav)

Typography & Spacing:
- Base font size: 16px
- Heading scale: 2xl > xl > lg > base
- Padding/margin: multiples of 4 (4px, 8px, 16px, etc.)
